&lt;p&gt;FIRST_VALUE(expr,[expr,...])&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;where it would evaluate all arguments in order, and return the first one.
This is for symmetry with LAST_VALUE, but also because sometimes it's more natural to write the expression you want to return first.&lt;/p&gt;
